# Commit Message Format Guide
# Follow Conventional Commits: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
#
# Format:
#   <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
#   <body>
#
#   <footer>
#
# Types: feat, fix, refactor, perf, test, docs, chore, ci, style, build
# Scopes: agent, api, ui, db, docs, skill (optional)
#
# EXAMPLE:
#
#   feat(agent): add batch processing for discovery phase
#   
#   Improve performance by processing user imports in batches instead
#   of one at a time. Prevents database transaction timeouts for large
#   imports.
#   
#   - Add DiscoveryFlowLimits configuration
#   - Implement batch insert method
#   - Add tests for atomicity
#   
#   Fixes #42
#
# RULES:
#
# • Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
# • Don't capitalize the first letter of subject
# • No period at end of subject
# • Subject: max 50 characters
# • Body: wrap at 72 characters
# • Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# • Reference issues with "Fixes #123" or "Related to #456"
#
# GOOD:
#   feat(ui): add floating chat widget
#   fix(db): resolve race condition in batch inserts
#   docs: update architecture diagram
#   chore: upgrade dependencies
#
# BAD:
#   update stuff
#   WIP
#   Fix bug
#   Added feature
#
